long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1168546 kscreen config when booted with both displays connected
Description of problem: Previously working multiple display configuration overwritten by reboot.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): kscreen-5.6.4-1.fc23.x86_64
How reproducible: Fully. Every reboot causes problem
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Have properly configured dual display or try to configure two displays 2. Both displays connected 3. Reboot system
Actual results: Both displays show same image (2nd screen image)
Expected results: Correct configuration is not destroyed. Able to configure multiple screens.
Additional info: Multiple display configuration was working as expected until I rebooted for unrelated issues. Upon reboot, both displays were mirrored. I noted that regardless of which display I chose in the System Settings tool, the "identify" button always reported the 2nd screen (HDMI3) on both displays.
Looking at .local/share/kscreen/<guid>, I saw that both displays showed "pos": {"x":0,"y":0}. Manually editing the file to set x=1920 on 2nd display, i.e., to the correct value, didn't persist across a reboot and had no effect.
Work-around: Disconnect 2nd display, reboot, plug in 2nd display, and configure via System Settings. The kscreen config file now correctly shows the 2nd display x=1920.
Created attachment 1168547 kscreen config when booted with only one display connected and 2nd added post-boot
uname -a: Linux closter.lombardsnest.com 4.5.6-200.fc23.x86_64 #1 SMP Wed Jun 1 21:28:20 UTC 2016 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 25 development cycle. Changing version to '25'.
Appears to be fixed with very recent update. Not sure which specific update fixed it as I try to keep up-to-date. But, it is clearly fixed with kscreen-5.7.2-1.fc23.x86_64
